IndyCar Glory, MSNBC Palace Drama, A Biden Insider Tells All
------------------------------------------------------------

Happy Friday and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon guide to=
 Puck=E2=80=99s
freshest reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni offers his bracing diagnosis of the Oscars=E2=
=80=99 diminishing relevance, arguing that the overt internationalization o=
f the voting body has alienated viewers by niche-ifying the nominations bey=
ond the mainstream=E2=80=94just as the lucrative telecast needs a shot of p=
opulism more than ever.

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Tara Palmeri convenes with longtime Jill Biden press =
secretary Michael LaRosa for a remarkably candid conversation about the Joe=
 Biden =E2=80=9Ccover-up.=E2=80=9D John Ourand gets on the horn with Fox Sp=
orts boss Eric Shanks to discuss his attempt to restore IndyCar to its form=
er glory. And for Inner Circle members, Lauren Sherman
breaks down why Gucci=E2=80=99s creative designer succession sweepstakes ar=
e so consequential to the future of the brand.

Meanwhile, on the pods: Matt is joined by WME partner Robert Newman on The =
Town to chew over the Oscars=E2=80=99 relevance problem. On Fashion People,=
 Lauren and comms guru Lucien Pag=C3=A8s debate how Americans and Europeans=
 approach fashion and style. On Impolitic, John Heilemann connects
with Michael McFaul, former U.S. ambassador to Russia, to dissect Trump=E2=
=80=99s machinations to end the war in Ukraine. And on The Powers That Be, =
Dylan Byers and Peter Hamby examine the turmoil brewing at 30 Rock after Re=
becca Kutler=E2=80=99s sweeping programming overhaul.

